3. More UBs. Create a UB manager which traces multiple UBs (specifically their constraints) along generation. For example for each statement L we generated: `ubManager.trace(L); -> `
	```
	void UBManager::TraceAndGenerateUBConstraints(IR l) {
		for (UBConstraintGen g : this->generators) {
			// One of g may be our IntegerUBConstraintGen which collects under-/over-flow constrates for integers.
			// The other one may be ArrayUBConstraintGen which collects UB constraints for arrays for example out-of-bounds access.
			g.GenerateConstraint(L);
		}
	}
	```
